# Salesforce CLI (`sf`) Command Reference

Canonical reference for the new-style `sf` CLI (oclif-based). Replaces legacy `sfdx` commands. Full source: https://github.com/salesforcecli/cli

---

## 🚨 MANDATORY: Retrieve BEFORE editing

**Local files are NOT the source of truth — `{{ORG_ALIAS}}` is.** Teammates and admins deploy directly to the org, so anything on disk may be stale. Before modifying ANY metadata (Apex, LWC, Aura, layouts, FlexiPages, OmniScripts, Integration Procedures, flows, fields, perm sets, etc.), **you MUST retrieve the component(s) first**:

```bash
sf project retrieve start --metadata <Type>:<Name> -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}         # single component
sf project retrieve start --manifest manifest/<feature>.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} # scoped manifest
```

Skipping this step silently overwrites newer org state on your next deploy. The `project retrieve start` section below has the full flag reference.

---

## Org Conventions

1. **Default target org is `{{ORG_ALIAS}}`** (sandbox). Every command in this repo assumes `-o {{ORG_ALIAS}}` (equivalent to `--target-org {{ORG_ALIAS}}`).
2. Confirm the org list with `sf org list --all` before destructive ops.
3. Source API version is **66.0**; package directory is `force-app/`.
4. Manifests live in `manifest/<feature>.xml` — create a NEW one per feature, never overwrite `apex.xml` / `mainpackage.xml`.
5. `--ignore-conflicts` is used in this repo because source tracking is not the source of truth — trust the manifest.
6. After ANY Apex execution, fetch logs (`sf apex get log --log-id recent`) and grep for `EXCEPTION|ERROR|FATAL`. See [`test-deploy-ruleset.mdc`](./test-deploy-ruleset.mdc).

