## Global Flags (available on most commands)

| Flag | Short | Purpose |
|------|-------|---------|
| `--target-org <alias>` | `-o` | Target org alias/username. Required unless `target-org` is set in config. **Most-used shortcut in this repo** (`-o {{ORG_ALIAS}}` everywhere). |
| `--target-dev-hub <alias>` | `-v` | Dev Hub alias (for scratch/package commands). |
| `--api-version <n>` | | Override the API version for this command. |
| `--json` | | Output machine-readable JSON (pipe to `jq`). |
| `--wait <minutes>` | `-w` | Poll/wait timeout for async ops. |
| `--async` | | Return immediately; check status via `resume`/`report`. |
| `--verbose` | | Extra logging. |
| `--concise` | | Trim output (deploy / test summaries). |
| `--no-prompt` | `-p` | Skip interactive confirmation (varies — sometimes `-r`, see per-topic tables). |
| `--flags-dir <dir>` | | Import flag values from a directory (advanced). |

> **Long form vs short form.** Every example below preserves the long form for readability. The per-topic "Common short flags" tables list the equivalent short forms — both are valid, and `sf` accepts them interchangeably. Short forms are case-sensitive.

> **Legacy aliases.** Most `sf` commands still accept their pre-unification aliases (`sf force apex execute`, `sf auth web login`, `sf auth list`, `sf force project create`, etc.). The aliases are documented in each plugin's `ALIASES` block. They're useful when reading older sfdx scripts but `sf <topic> <verb>` is the canonical form for new code.

