## Topic: `project` — Deploy / Retrieve / Convert

### Common short flags (`deploy-retrieve` plugin)

| Long | Short | Used by |
|------|-------|---------|
| `--target-org` | `-o` | All deploy/retrieve commands |
| `--api-version` | `-a` | `project deploy start/validate`, `project retrieve start` |
| `--manifest` | `-x` | `project deploy start/validate`, `project retrieve start`, `project generate manifest` |
| `--metadata` | `-m` | `project deploy start/validate`, `project retrieve start`, `project delete source`, `project generate manifest` |
| `--source-dir` | `-d` | `project deploy start/validate`, `project retrieve start`, `project delete source`, `project generate manifest` |
| `--ignore-conflicts` | `-c` | `project deploy start/validate`, `project retrieve start`, `project delete source` |
| `--ignore-warnings` | `-g` | `project deploy start/validate` |
| `--ignore-errors` | `-r` | `project deploy start/validate` |
| `--test-level` | `-l` | `project deploy start/validate`, `project deploy pipeline *` |
| `--tests` | `-t` | `project deploy start/validate`, `project deploy pipeline *` |
| `--wait` | `-w` | All deploy/retrieve commands that poll |
| `--job-id` | `-i` | `project deploy cancel/quick/report/resume`, `project retrieve resume` |
| `--use-most-recent` | `-r` | `project deploy report/resume` |
| `--source-dir` (delete) | `-p` | `project delete source` (where it's `-p`, not `-d`) |
| `--name` | `-n` | `project generate manifest`, `project deploy pipeline start` |
| `--output-dir` | `-d` | `project generate manifest` |

### Deploy (source → org)
```bash
# Single-class syntax validation (fastest feedback)
sf project deploy start --metadata ApexClass:MyClass -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} --ignore-conflicts
sf project deploy start -m ApexClass:MyClass -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -c                         # Short form

# Manifest-driven deploy with targeted tests (PREFERRED for Apex work)
sf project deploy start \
  --manifest './manifest/my-feature.xml' \
  -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} \
  --test-level RunSpecifiedTests \
  --tests MyClassTest \
  --ignore-conflicts \
  --wait 10

# Same deploy, fully short-form
sf project deploy start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -l RunSpecifiedTests -t MyClassTest -c -w 10

# Deploy a source dir
sf project deploy start -d force-app/main/default/classes -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project deploy start --source-dir force-app/main/default/classes -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}

# Multiple metadata types / patterns (wildcards require quotes)
sf project deploy start -m 'ApexClass:MyApex*' --ignore-warnings -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project deploy start -m CustomObject -m ApexClass -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}

# Concise / verbose / dry-run
sf project deploy start -d force-app -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} --concise                          # Trim output
sf project deploy start -d force-app -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} --verbose                          # Component-by-component
sf project deploy start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} --dry-run -l RunSpecifiedTests -t MyClassTest

# Coverage formatters + JUnit (CI friendly)
sf project deploy start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} \
  -l RunSpecifiedTests -t MyClassTest \
  --coverage-formatters cobertura --coverage-formatters html-spa \
  --junit --results-dir ./test-results

# Destructive changes (delete components on deploy)
sf project deploy start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml \
  --pre-destructive-changes ./manifest/destructiveChangesPre.xml \
  --post-destructive-changes ./manifest/destructiveChangesPost.xml \
  --purge-on-delete -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}

# Metadata-API zip / dir deploy (instead of source format)
sf project deploy start --metadata-dir mdapi_output --single-package -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}

# Validate-only (no commit) — produces a deploy ID for later quick-deploy
sf project deploy validate --manifest './manifest/my-feature.xml' -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} --test-level RunSpecifiedTests --tests MyClassTest
sf project deploy validate -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -l RunSpecifiedTests -t MyClassTest -w 10  # Short form

# Promote a validated deploy
sf project deploy quick --job-id <deploy-id> -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project deploy quick -i <deploy-id> -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -w 10

# Preview / cancel / resume / report
sf project deploy preview -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project deploy preview -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                 # Preview a specific manifest
sf project deploy cancel -i <id> -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                                        # -i ≡ --job-id
sf project deploy cancel --use-most-recent -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                              # Most recent job
sf project deploy report -i <id> -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project deploy report -r -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                                             # -r ≡ --use-most-recent
sf project deploy resume -i <id> -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -w 10
sf project deploy resume -r -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
```

**Test levels:** `NoTestRun`, `RunSpecifiedTests`, `RunLocalTests`, `RunAllTestsInOrg`, `RunRelevantTests`.

> `RunRelevantTests` (added in API v62.0+) runs only the tests Salesforce determines are relevant to the changed components. Useful for incremental deploys; not all orgs/edition combos support it.

### Retrieve (org → source)
```bash
sf project retrieve start --manifest './manifest/my-feature.xml' -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project retrieve start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                  # Short form
sf project retrieve start -m "ApexClass:MyClass" -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project retrieve start -m ApexClass -m CustomObject -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                  # Multiple types
sf project retrieve start -d force-app/main/default/classes -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project retrieve start -d force-app -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} --ignore-conflicts -w 30
sf project retrieve start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml --target-metadata-dir ./mdapi_out -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}     # Retrieve as MDAPI
sf project retrieve start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml --zip-file-name retrieved.zip --unzip -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} # Zip output
sf project retrieve start --package-name MyPackage -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                      # Retrieve installed managed pkg
sf project retrieve preview -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project retrieve resume -i <job-id> -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                                  # Resume an async retrieve
sf project retrieve resume -r -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                                           # Most recent retrieve
```

### Metadata API names cheat sheet (for `-m` / `-x`)

The `-m` / `--metadata` flag uses the **Metadata API type name**, which is NOT always what the component is called in the UI. Get this wrong and the deploy/retrieve silently misses your file. Use `sf org list metadata-types -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}` for the authoritative list; the table below covers the high-traffic {{ORG_NAME}} components.

| UI/file term | Metadata API name | Address form (`-m Type:Name`) | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Apex class | `ApexClass` | `ApexClass:MyClass` | The `.cls`; the `-meta.xml` rides along automatically. |
| Apex trigger | `ApexTrigger` | `ApexTrigger:MyTrigger` | |
| Apex test suite | `ApexTestSuite` | `ApexTestSuite:MySuite` | |
| LWC (Lightning Web Component) | `LightningComponentBundle` | `LightningComponentBundle:myCmp` | NOT `LWC` / `LightningWebComponent`. Retrieves the whole bundle (`.js`, `.html`, `.css`, `.xml`). |
| Aura component | `AuraDefinitionBundle` | `AuraDefinitionBundle:myAura` | NOT `Aura` / `LightningComponent`. Whole bundle. |
| OmniScript | `OmniScript` | `OmniScript:OrderEntry_OnlineOrder_English_3` | Filename convention is `<Type>_<SubType>_<Lang>_<Version>`. Member name = the part BEFORE `.os-meta.xml`. |
| Integration Procedure | `OmniIntegrationProcedure` | `OmniIntegrationProcedure:OrderProcessing_Procedure_3` | `_Procedure_<Version>` suffix. Member name = part before `.oip-meta.xml`. |
| DataRaptor | `OmniDataTransform` | `OmniDataTransform:DR_OrderProcessing_LookupAccount` | Covers Extract / Load / Transform / Turbo. |
| FlexCard | `OmniUiCard` (newer) or `FlexCard` (legacy) | `OmniUiCard:OrderSummaryCard_English_1` | Check `force-app/main/default/omniUiCard/` vs `flexCards/` for which your org uses. |
| Vlocity Interaction Configuration | `OmniInteractionConfig` | `OmniInteractionConfig:OrderEntryConfig` | Lives under `omniInteractionConfigurations/`. |
| FlexiPage (Lightning record/app/home page) | `FlexiPage` | `FlexiPage:Account_Record_Page` | NOT `LightningPage`. Name matches the file without `.flexipage-meta.xml`. |
| Page layout | `Layout` | `Layout:Account-Account Layout` | **Address form uses a hyphen between object and layout name**, NOT a dot. |
| Record type | `RecordType` | `RecordType:Account.B2B_Customer` | Object.DeveloperName. |
| Custom field | `CustomField` | `CustomField:Account.Customer_Tier__c` | Object.FieldApiName, including `__c` suffix on custom fields. |
| Custom object | `CustomObject` | `CustomObject:Order__c` (custom) or `CustomObject:Account` (standard) | Standard objects retrieve their full describe (fields + RT + layouts). |
| Validation rule | `ValidationRule` | `ValidationRule:Account.Require_Customer_Tier` | Object.RuleName. |
| Workflow rule | `WorkflowRule` | `WorkflowRule:Account.NotifyOwnerOnTierChange` | (workflows are deprecated; you usually want `Flow`). |
| Flow | `Flow` | `Flow:Notify_Owner_On_Tier_Change` | A specific version: `Flow:Notify_Owner_On_Tier_Change-3`. |
| Flow Definition | `FlowDefinition` | `FlowDefinition:Notify_Owner_On_Tier_Change` | The activation pointer; needed when promoting a specific Flow version. |
| Web link (Case button etc.) | `WebLink` | `WebLink:Case.Escalate_To_Tier_2` | Object.ButtonName. The most-missed addressing form. |
| Quick Action | `QuickAction` | `QuickAction:Account.Log_A_Call` | For object-specific QAs. Global: `QuickAction:My_Global_Action`. |
| Permission set | `PermissionSet` | `PermissionSet:Order_Manager` | |
| Permission set group | `PermissionSetGroup` | `PermissionSetGroup:Order_Team_All` | |
| Profile | `Profile` | `Profile:Standard User` | Profile name has spaces — quote it: `'Profile:System Administrator'`. |
| Custom label | `CustomLabel` | `CustomLabel:Welcome_Banner_Text` | Each label is its own member — there's no "all labels" bundle. |
| Custom metadata type | `CustomMetadata` | `CustomMetadata:Pricing_Tier_Config.Bronze` | Each RECORD is a member. To grab the type definition + all records, use both `CustomObject:Pricing_Tier_Config__mdt` AND `CustomMetadata:Pricing_Tier_Config.*`. |
| Static resource | `StaticResource` | `StaticResource:CompanyLogo` | |
| Email template | `EmailTemplate` | `EmailTemplate:unfiled$public/Welcome_Email` | Folder path BEFORE the slash; template DeveloperName after. |
| Report | `Report` | `Report:Sales_Reports/Weekly_Pipeline` | Same folder/name pattern as email templates. |
| Dashboard | `Dashboard` | `Dashboard:Sales_Dashboards/Pipeline_Overview` | |
| Lightning App | `CustomApplication` | `CustomApplication:OrderManagement` | NOT `LightningApp`. |
| Connected App | `ConnectedApp` | `ConnectedApp:OrderApi_OAuth` | |
| Named credential | `NamedCredential` | `NamedCredential:ExternalPricingApi` | |
| Custom tab | `CustomTab` | `CustomTab:Order__c` (custom objects auto-tab on api name) / `CustomTab:Orders_Console` | |
| Translation | `Translations` | `Translations:en_US` | Per-locale member. |
| Custom translation | `CustomObjectTranslation` | `CustomObjectTranslation:Account-en_US` | Object-locale form. |

> **Naming in the table is illustrative.** The `OrderProcessing_*` / `Order_Manager` / `Customer_Tier__c` style names are just placeholders that match the file-name convention each metadata type follows in a typical Salesforce org. Substitute your org's actual component names.

> **Wildcard form for `-m`.** `sf project retrieve start -m 'OmniScript:OrderEntry_*' -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}` retrieves every OmniScript whose name starts with `OrderEntry_`. Quotes are required so the shell doesn't expand the asterisk.

> **Bundle vs. file gotcha.** `-m LightningComponentBundle:myCmp` grabs the WHOLE bundle. There is no way to retrieve a single `.js` inside an LWC via the metadata API — same applies to Aura and OmniScript.

> **`-m` vs. `-d` choice.** Use `-m Type:Name` when you know the metadata identity (preferred — survives renames of local folder structure). Use `-d force-app/main/default/<dir>` only when you want everything under a directory.

Common multi-component retrieve patterns (substitute your real component names):
```bash
# OmniStudio component + its dependencies (the cache-bust dance entry point)
sf project retrieve start \
  -m OmniIntegrationProcedure:OrderProcessing_Procedure_3 \
  -m OmniDataTransform:DR_OrderProcessing_LookupAccount \
  -m ApexClass:OrderProcessingPostProcess \
  -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}

# A whole Case-button feature (button + OmniScript + IPs + DRs it calls)
sf project retrieve start \
  -m WebLink:Case.Escalate_To_Tier_2 \
  -m OmniScript:CaseEscalation_Tier2_English_4 \
  -m OmniIntegrationProcedure:CaseEscalation_Procedure_4 \
  -m OmniIntegrationProcedure:CaseEscalation_LogicContainer_Procedure_2 \
  -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}

# Permission set + the custom field(s) it grants access to
sf project retrieve start \
  -m PermissionSet:Order_Manager \
  -m CustomField:Account.Sales_Region__c \
  -m CustomField:Account.Customer_Tier__c \
  -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}

# Layout + record type + the fields it shows
sf project retrieve start \
  -m Layout:Account-B2B_Customer_Layout \
  -m RecordType:Account.B2B_Customer \
  -m CustomField:Account.Customer_Tier__c \
  -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
```

