## Topic: `plugins`, `autocomplete`, `dev`

### Common short flags (`plugins` core + `dev` plugin)

| Long | Short | Used by |
|------|-------|---------|
| `--name` | `-n` | `dev generate command` |
| `--script` | `-s` | `dev convert script` |
| `--file-name` | `-f` | `dev convert messages` |
| `--source-dir` | `-s` | `dev audit messages` |
| `--messages-dir` | `-m` | `dev audit messages` |
| `--project-dir` | `-p` | `dev audit messages`, `dev convert messages` |
| `--dry-run` | `-d` | `dev generate flag` |
| `--event` | `-e` | `dev generate hook` |
| `--plugin` | `-p` | `plugins trust verify`, `doctor --plugin` |
| `--command` | `-c` | `doctor --command` |
| `--output-dir` | `-d` | `doctor --output-dir` |
| `--create-issue` | `-i` | `doctor --create-issue` |

```bash
sf plugins                                # List installed plugins
sf plugins discover                       # Curated 3rd-party list (from plugin-marketplace)
sf plugins install @salesforce/plugin-foo
sf plugins install @salesforce/plugin-foo@1.2.3                            # Pinned version
sf plugins uninstall @salesforce/plugin-foo
sf plugins update
sf plugins reset --hard
sf plugins link /path/to/local/plugin     # For plugin dev
sf plugins trust verify --plugin @salesforce/plugin-foo
sf plugins trust verify -p @salesforce/plugin-foo

sf autocomplete                           # Auto-detect shell
sf autocomplete zsh                       # Prints setup for your shell (bash/zsh/powershell)
sf autocomplete bash
sf autocomplete --refresh-cache           # Refresh tab-completion cache

# Plugin development (only if authoring a plugin)
sf dev generate plugin
sf dev generate plugin --dry-run
sf dev generate command --name my:cmd
sf dev generate command -n my:cmd                                          # Short form
sf dev generate command -n my:cmd --no-nuts --no-unit                      # Skip auto-generated tests
sf dev generate flag --command my:cmd
sf dev generate flag -d                                                     # Dry-run (preview the new flag code)
sf dev generate hook --event sf:env:list                                    # Generate a hook for an existing event
sf dev generate library                                                     # Scaffold a library plugin
sf dev audit messages                                                       # Default ./messages and ./src
sf dev audit messages -m ./messages -s ./src -p ./my-plugin                 # Explicit dirs
sf dev convert messages --file-or-dir messages/
sf dev convert messages -f my-command.json -p ./my-plugin                   # Single message file
sf dev convert script --source old.sh --destination new.sh                  # sfdx → sf migration
sf dev convert script -s old.sh                                             # Short form (writes old-converted.sh)
```

