## Quick-Reference Cheatsheet

Each block below shows the long-form invocation followed by its short-form equivalent. Both are valid — pick whichever is easier to type/read.

```bash
# 1. Validate Apex syntax
sf project deploy start --metadata ApexClass:MyClass -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} --ignore-conflicts
sf project deploy start -m ApexClass:MyClass -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -c                         # Short form

# 2. Deploy feature with tests
sf project deploy start --manifest './manifest/my-feature.xml' -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} \
    --test-level RunSpecifiedTests --tests MyClassTest --ignore-conflicts --wait 10
sf project deploy start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} \
    -l RunSpecifiedTests -t MyClassTest -c -w 10                                   # Short form

# 3. Run a single test with coverage (only reliable way to verify %)
sf apex run test --class-names MyClassTest -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} \
    --synchronous --code-coverage --result-format human --wait 10
sf apex run test -n MyClassTest -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -y -c -r human -w 10                   # Short form

# 4. Retrieve logs and grep for failures (MANDATORY after any Apex run)
sf apex get log --log-id recent -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} | grep -E "(EXCEPTION|ERROR|FATAL)"
sf apex get log -i recent -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} | grep -E "(EXCEPTION|ERROR|FATAL)"          # Short form

# 5. Ad-hoc SOQL
sf data query -q "SELECT Id FROM IndividualApplication WHERE RecordType.DeveloperName='PRM_PDMManualChange' LIMIT 5" -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf data query -q "SELECT Id FROM IndividualApplication LIMIT 5" -r csv --output-file out.csv -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}   # Save as CSV

# 6. Describe an object
sf sobject describe -s HealthcareFacility -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} | head -80

# 7. Retrieve a component before editing (MANDATORY per repo convention)
sf project retrieve start --metadata ApexClass:MyClass -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}
sf project retrieve start -m ApexClass:MyClass -o {{ORG_ALIAS}}                          # Short form
sf project retrieve start -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -c -w 30         # Manifest + ignore-conflicts

# 8. Validate-only (produce a deploy ID for later quick-deploy)
sf project deploy validate -x ./manifest/my-feature.xml -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} \
    -l RunSpecifiedTests -t MyClassTest -w 10
sf project deploy quick -i <deploy-id> -o {{ORG_ALIAS}} -w 10                            # Promote validated deploy
```

